Ardour is an application to fit the needs of musicians under Linux.
It is designed to be a fully functional professional audio application,
that uses the professional sound server jack for sound i/o.

soundtouch, libwebsockets, cppunit and lua are optional dependencies.

This package is essentially the same as the one provided by
Matteo Bernardini at SlackBuilds.org, but usually installs a more
updated version of Ardour. Do not install both at the same time.

Note:
Although you can download the sources provided in this package
github, as general practice you should download them directly
from Ardour.org.
